# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Optional: one-tap Google Drive sign-in backup & restore.
#
# Leave this UNSET to use the zero-setup "Save / Share to Drive" fallback
# (exports a backup file you drop into the Google Drive app). Set it to enable
# full in-app Google sign-in that backs up/restores to a "Riyaz Backups" folder.
#
# How to get a client ID (free):
#   1. Google Cloud Console → APIs & Services → Credentials.
#   2. Create an "OAuth client ID" of type "Web application".
#   3. Under "Authorized JavaScript origins" add your origin(s), e.g.
#        http://localhost:3000  and  https://your-app.vercel.app
#   4. Enable the "Google Drive API" for the project.
#   5. Paste the client ID below. Scope used is the non-sensitive `drive.file`
#      (the app only ever sees files it creates), so no app verification needed.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
